Mesirow Financial Chief Jim Tyree Dies of Stomach Cancer at 53

-- B y   J e r a n   W i t t e n s t e i n
-- 
2011-03-17T03:15:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-17/mesirow-financial-chief-jim-tyree-dies-of-stomach-cancer-at-53.html
Jim Tyree, the chief executive
officer and chairman of Mesirow Financial Inc., has died of
stomach cancer. He was 53.  Tyree “made an indelible impression on each of us at
Mesirow Financial and our hearts are broken,” the company said
in a statement on its website.   Tyree became chairman and chief executive officer in 1994
after joining Mesirow in 1980, according to the company’s
website. He earned B.A. and M.B.A. degrees from Illinois State
University.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jeran Wittenstein at 
 jwittenstei1@bloomberg.net  